  },
  "pronunciation_dictionary_locators": [
    {
      "pronunciation_dictionary_id": "AhK3J8mZDRoShxfoJLk6",
      "version_id": "pFvyQBbxEBKyF7C3IHpy"
    }
  ],
  "inter_chunk_silence_ms": 650,
  "chunks": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "Most Claude Max subscribers hit their limit by noon \u2014 and they never figure out why.",
      "checksum": "sha256:40f67e48a55104c17faa076918af564adbeaa5094d7af11fff5dc1a86390c29d",
      "wav": "chunk-00.wav",
      "duration": 4.597551020408163,
      "word_count": 16,
      "words_offset": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "text": "You're paying a hundred or two hundred dollars a month for Claude Max.",
      "checksum": "sha256:1040cb45f2a0e52bad746dbe71b6c5000aed9ac1a9cbc365386eeef2900cd6e4",
      "wav": "chunk-01.wav",
      "duration": 3.6687528344671203,
      "word_count": 13,
      "words_offset": 16
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "text": "But here's what Anthropic doesn't put on the pricing page: a bloated CLAUDE.md file costs you tokens on every single turn.",
      "checksum": "sha256:6a189ca42d5969c125157ef73ed4074fcae94f49e5d7b792d6ca5db56e4b1dba",
      "wav": "chunk-02.wav",
      "duration": 7.244625850340136,
      "word_count": 21,
      "words_offset": 29
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "text": "Not just once. Every message. Five thousand tokens of CLAUDE.md instructions means five thousand tokens burned before you've typed a word.",
      "checksum": "sha256:c514b031562c338fb1c69b6c529c8d7b00929710557a06cac90d36852183bfb1",
      "wav": "chunk-03.wav",
      "duration": 7.476825396825397,
      "word_count": 21,
      "words_offset": 50
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "text": "There are five fixes that actually move the needle.",
      "checksum": "sha256:9701dd8bd63fb5cbbf279e51ba94bec281d8f7c6b4cc4c15b938e87e59321757",
      "wav": "chunk-04.wav",
      "duration": 2.8792743764172335,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 71
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "text": "Fix one. Trim your CLAUDE.md below two hundred lines.",
      "checksum": "sha256:fea3812a965d5716450c28a5f9a49eec8ce79ab13e149f28797129f79018e134",
      "wav": "chunk-05.wav",
      "duration": 3.297233560090703,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 80
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "text": "Most developers bloat it to six hundred lines over time \u2014 rules for debugging, rules for testing, rules for formatting.",
      "checksum": "sha256:75d94aa949979db4e1f68e1b1afbb0636949477351d77bb1ca128c69bdc0facd",
      "wav": "chunk-06.wav",
      "duration": 7.012426303854875,
      "word_count": 20,
      "words_offset": 89
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "text": "But Claude reads the whole file on every message, even when you're just fixing a C S S typo.",
      "checksum": "sha256:2fff67fbb2539770d51c45638c89d2ce705506d1da91ffd04b8551edffcba927",
      "wav": "chunk-07.wav",
      "duration": 5.201269841269841,
      "word_count": 19,
      "words_offset": 109
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "text": "Keep only what's essential. Cut the rest.",
      "checksum": "sha256:8cb45884f64ce0aac0d53dea671717c64a47b99b40de9299516db5dccc75acf4",
      "wav": "chunk-08.wav",
      "duration": 2.2755555555555556,
      "word_count": 7,
      "words_offset": 128
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "text": "Fix two. Use dot-claudeignore. It works exactly like dot-gitignore.",
      "checksum": "sha256:3d8b6b3d2ab63cde9e52151406d90d8ce942c1181d669b1642734323c100cfc2",
      "wav": "chunk-09.wav",
      "duration": 3.947392290249433,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 135
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "text": "Add your node-modules, your build folders, your generated files.",
      "checksum": "sha256:811315428d7ea7d6a93dad03de2921b42e919e1867b475c02626678c34c3605b",
      "wav": "chunk-10.wav",
      "duration": 3.9938321995464854,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 144
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "text": "When Claude can't see those files, it can't accidentally load them \u2014 and your context stays clean.",
      "checksum": "sha256:7140edec8ce0c55accc07247b7c8f3bd0f6c7c0bd8694b8b57f2fb1100c2e287",
      "wav": "chunk-11.wav",
      "duration": 5.804988662131519,
      "word_count": 17,
      "words_offset": 153
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "text": "Fix three. Specific beats vague. \"Fix the bug\" sends Claude hunting across your entire codebase.",
      "checksum": "sha256:92875d456914d81df472b2805b3ca0a468cbf638424926333c3209503f166206",
      "wav": "chunk-12.wav",
      "duration": 7.1053061224489795,
      "word_count": 15,
      "words_offset": 170
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "text": "\"Fix the J W T validation in src/auth/validate.ts line forty-two where expired tokens aren't rejected\" goes straight to the problem.",
      "checksum": "sha256:3ebfdf561335623c40bf63f9fb2866aed9dc6d0c61c82616210e101d5f2ce5ea",
      "wav": "chunk-13.wav",
      "duration": 9.287981859410431,
      "word_count": 20,
      "words_offset": 185
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "text": "The difference can be ten times fewer tokens consumed.\n\nFix four.",
      "checksum": "sha256:e4a6ff477c1e8d297410d7bb4fbb2adc666704412a9b704e40ff9f8aafde4997",
      "wav": "chunk-14.wav",
      "duration": 3.622312925170068,
      "word_count": 11,
      "words_offset": 205
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "text": "Run slash-compact before your context fills.",
      "checksum": "sha256:eccb51ebcc5655206ad8e0bbea37105998adb15524c34d406dd35763b7945465",
      "wav": "chunk-15.wav",
      "duration": 2.507755102040816,
      "word_count": 6,
      "words_offset": 216
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "text": "Claude Code auto-compacts when you hit about eighty-three percent of the context window.",
      "checksum": "sha256:2cceff19d61feedabc4e6e7827b305a9154a5f129fbdbd05be503c57fb0c0a06",
      "wav": "chunk-16.wav",
      "duration": 4.73687074829932,
      "word_count": 13,
      "words_offset": 222
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "text": "But by then you've already paid for all those tokens.",
      "checksum": "sha256:371c63ca51305bba1b1730c33698aedae6d84c1a81d00c45925f5be76413c323",
      "wav": "chunk-17.wav",
      "duration": 2.786394557823129,
      "word_count": 10,
      "words_offset": 235
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "text": "Running slash-compact manually at the halfway point keeps sessions sharp and cheap.",
      "checksum": "sha256:82a5125819d81bd9bd2aab9036b0ec2279cf6dee3bbf808b5910683083262045",
      "wav": "chunk-18.wav",
      "duration": 4.365351473922902,
      "word_count": 12,
      "words_offset": 245
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "text": "Fix five. Watch your images. A full screenshot passed to Claude costs about thirteen hundred tokens.",
      "checksum": "sha256:cd2d0669cb20199dd1a355e6a7b468ad2cfb1fd9709ad3c8b58927ed621dafed",
      "wav": "chunk-19.wav",
      "duration": 7.291065759637188,
      "word_count": 16,
      "words_offset": 257
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "text": "A tight crop of the relevant section? Under a hundred. Same information, thirteen times cheaper.",
      "checksum": "sha256:fff29a690a1d9a99c650f3ecb2d307df3e4c6f82e11cb6ec4abd707d7461fae9",
      "wav": "chunk-20.wav",
      "duration": 5.6656689342403626,
      "word_count": 15,
      "words_offset": 273
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "text": "The Max plan gives you headroom. These five fixes make sure you actually use it for the work that matters, not the filler your project drags in by default.",
      "checksum": "sha256:83fc9d2262aba72c0f5f22d119aae8a734d929d42321d50777388a2ea8a2cbf2",
      "wav": "chunk-21.wav",
      "duration": 8.544943310657596,
      "word_count": 29,
      "words_offset": 288
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "text": "If you want to learn more about A I, check out the dynamous.ai community.",
      "checksum": "sha256:11103ce9f04648e297b0f9cd6e8075323647e9cb83506d3f92d6e3dcbba8e7fe",
      "wav": "chunk-22.wav",
      "duration": 4.504671201814059,
      "word_count": 14,
      "words_offset": 317
    }
  ]
}